<br>
I do see your point that it seems that the giant US and her allies can't take a simple little town.<br>
<br>
The big BUT...is the fact that if the coalition didn't want to rebuild the country and attempt to allow the citizens realize this time we WERE there to help, and weren't going to step aside, they would just level the city, not worrying about any civilian casualties or civilian structure destruction.<br>
<br>
Any urban warfare is probably the most costly (by life) and difficult that there is.  History shows this.  Germany was repulsed in Stalingrad... I'm not sure on numbers, but I'd imagine the Russians had far more, though the German's were far superior in technological aspects.<br>
<br>
Fast forward to today...paralels can be drawn of course between US/Germany Iraq/Russia.<br>
<br>
If things don't go the way we hope (Iraqi's realize we ARE there to help this time) then there are going to be too many of the worlds boys and girls sacraficing everything for what they fight for.  Heaven help us this isn't the case, but it is a possibility of course.<br>
<br>
God bless our men and women walking into the Valley, and may they come out again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nitzen>Nitzen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/25/03 6:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We have a problem</span><hr size=1> The problem is we are fighting using Geneva Convention rules of 1949...but the enemy is not. The fake surrender..they continue to break many rules of engagement knowing we won't hurt the civilians.  The army wears civilian cloths to move around within the city. etc etc.<br>
